ent splashing then cook <b>7 min\/120°C\/\/speed 1<b>. Transfer to a bowl and allow to cool for 1 hour."},{"content":"To make carimañolas, divide cassava mixture into 8 balls. Flatten each ball across the palm, place about 1 tablespoon of filling in the centre and gently fold cassava over to enclose filling. Shape into a diamond and finish off neatly."},{"content":"In a frying pan, add oil to a depth of 2 cm and heat to frying temperature, around 130°C. Cook carimañolas for approx. 3 minutes each, turning often. Drain on paper towels, and serve warm or cool."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Cassava is also known as yucca or manioc. It is a very versatile starchy root vegetable, popular in South America and Africa.","Serve meat patties as a party platter, or serve 2 each as a main course.","The carimañolas can be made ahead and frozen. Allow them to cool completely to room temperature, and then spread out on a metal tray to freeze. When they have frozen, place in resealable freezer bags and return to freezer. This keeps them separate.","Serve with a tomato salsa: place <b>1 tomato<b>, <b>1 red<b> chilli, <b>80 g olive<b> oil, <b>30 g lemon<b> juice, <b>1 garlic<b> clove and <b>10 g parsley<b>  in mixing bowl and chop <b><strong>5 sec\/speed 5<\/strong><b>.","Instead of the meat filling, use <b>150 g<b> diced mozzarella cheese for a vegetarian option."],"basicInfo":["medium","25m","2h","8 pieces"]}